How to use the app
Step 1 — Gmail App Password (required)

Go to myaccount.google.com/apppasswords (needs 2FA enabled)
Create an app password for "Mail"
Use that 16-character password — not your regular Gmail password
Step 2 — Email file format

Each .email file in the emails/ directory follows this format:

to: recipient@example.com
subject: Your Subject Here
Body text goes here.
Multiple lines are fine.
Step 3 — UI workflow

Enter your Gmail address + App Password
Enter the directory path containing your .email files (or leave blank to use the bundled emails/ folder)
Click Load Email Files to preview them
Click Send All Pending or send individually per row
